subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen
(
Fig. 1d
). S1 black, but ventral third yellow; S2 black with broad yellow band laterally, from anteroventral corner over auricle towards posterior margin, which is narrowly black. S3 black with large anterolateral yellow markings that just connect to each other anteriorly over dorsal carina. S4–7 black with paired antero-dorsal spots, small on S4–6, but larger on S7. S8–10 black. The dorsal side of S10 curving downward in between the cerci to form a small nipple-like protrusion, not visible in lateral view (
Fig. 3d
).
